attachments.title: Why Facts Don’t Change Our Minds
attachments.text: New discoveries about the human mind show the limitations of reason.
attachments.fallback: The New Yorker: Why Facts Don’t Change Our Minds

text: One tidbit from the article about breaking confirmation bias: getting people to talk/think through their understanding of a position tends to temper their commitment to that view, and sways them to a more moderate perspective.
